cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as text classification. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new architecture for text processing using deep convolutional networks. Additionally, since the architecture is inspired by deep convolutional networks used in computer vision, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the model using backpropagation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Finally, since the model involves a large number of layers, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
